WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.400 size:80%
<v Tony Groom ><b>Tony Groom</b>
So the fire started way down this valley, it’s a place called Sarabah.

00:04.000 --> 00:09.000 size:80%
<v Tony Groom><b>Tony Groom</b>
And then on one particular day all the elements conspired to turn it into a raging inferno.

00:09.300 --> 00:15.000 size:80%
<v Tony Groom><b>Tony Groom</b>
The westerly wind, the temperatures, the dryness – and it raced up the mountain and destroyed the lodge and the houses.

00:18.500 --> 00:26.000 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
I don’t know what it must have been like to be a firey here that night but I imagine it would've been like a tsunami wave coming up the hill.

00:28.000 --> 00:32.000 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
The whole community has handled a shockwave. 

00:32.500 --> 00:37.600 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
We've actually been living in a war zone – that’s how it felt – right from coming back. 

00:38.500 --> 00:44.000 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
Firetrucks right through the night. Water bombers, helicopters, every day. 

00:45.500 --> 00:51.000 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
It’s been quite strange and I can see why you get PTSD from

00:51.100 --> 00:54.000 size:80%
<v Lisa Groom><b>Lisa Groom</b>
hearing certain things, and hearing choppers in the air.